<item>
            <title>[HTTPCORE-429] pool statistics don&apos;t expose all &apos;pending&apos; requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCORE-429</link>
                <project id="12310340" key="HTTPCORE">HttpComponents HttpCore</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During a performance run i noticed that the async http client was causing OOM exceptions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After enabling pool statistics, i did not see a big &apos;queue&apos; in the pool (the &apos;org.apache.http.pool.PoolStats#getPending&apos; method always returns a small number)&lt;br/&gt;
However, after some memory profiling it noticed that the pool has a lot of pending leaseRequests, but those requests are not exposed in the poolstats. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the org.apache.http.pool.PoolStats#getPending should also include the leaseRequest count.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
